<DOC><DOCNO> DOE2-39-1251 </DOCNO><TEXT>Sarcoidosis is a multisystemic disease and has diverse presentations whichmakes the diagnosis a little difficult. Gallium is being used to diagnoseactive sites of involvement. Whole body can be imaged by gallium scintigraphyusing a gamma camera aligned to a moving table and tomographic camera.The purpose of this study is to compare the efficacy of gallium scanningby two whole body scanning techniques in detecting various sites of activesarcoidosis. 4 refs.; 2 tabs. Contains index of authors and subject index</TEXT></DOC>